    "body": "**<sub><sub>![P1 Badge](https://img.shields.io/badge/P1-orange?style=flat)</sub></sub>  Wait on a detail-only selector in drill-in story**\n\n`findByText(\"@alice\")` is still ambiguous here and can resolve against the list row before the detail view mounts, because the list itself renders `@${user.username}` in `UserRow` (`site/src/pages/AgentsPage/AgentSettingsPageView.tsx`, subtitle prop). That means the next synchronous `getByText(\"Alice Liddell\")`/`getByText(\"@alice\")` assertions can still race exactly like before in Chromatic. Use a selector that exists only in the detail panel (or assert list disappearance first) so this wait actually gates on the transition.\n\nUseful? React with \ud83d\udc4d\u00a0/ \ud83d\udc4e.",
